---
import Layout from "../layouts/main.astro";
import Info from "../components/mdx/Info.astro";
---

<style lang="scss">
  @import "../styles/imports.scss";
  main {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 1.5rem;

    @media (max-width: $iPad) {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  aside {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
    justify-content: start;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-size: smaller;

    @media (max-width: $iPad) {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  a.badge {
    @include underlined-links;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.25rem;
    display: block;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 5px;
    border: 1px solid var(--linkColor);

    &:hover img.badgelogo {
      filter: brightness(1.3);
    }
  }
  img.badgelogo {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    box-shadow: none;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .space {
    margin: 2rem 0.5rem 2rem 3rem;
  }
</style>
<Layout>
  <main>
    <article>
      <h3>Hi, Frank L. Quednau here</h3>
      <p>
        I've been <a href="/tags/site">maintaining</a> this <a
          href="/posts/the-one-where-all-the-stuff-is-put-on-github"
          >online presence</a
        > since about the year 1997. I work in software development, about the
        first 12 years of my career in consulting positions, and for the past 10
        years in product development (with a small stint in the <em
          >"Enterprise"</em
        >).
      </p>
      <p>
        The last 5 years I've been <em>software gardening</em> at <a
          href="https://aheadintranet.com">ahead</a
        >, playing an important role in taking the company from 0 to almost 90
        happy customers and sustaining a company of about 15 people.
      </p>
      <p>
        The <a href="/posts/the-realfiction-manifesto"
          >realfiction manifesto from 2006</a
        >
         gives you some background about this website. While I still share the
        sentiment of the important entanglement between reality and fiction that
        drives human progress forward, with time this site became more of an
        outlet of things surrounding my software world, with short intermezzos
        that dabble into other areas of interest.
      </p>
      <hr />
      <Info>
        <div class="space">
          If you want to do me something good, here's my <a
            href="https://www.amazon.de/hz/wishlist/ls/1FR8NN43G98BJ?ref_=wl_share"
            >amazon wishlist</a
          >.
        </div>
      </Info>
    </article>
    <aside>
      <a class="badge" href="https://freiburg.social/@flq">
        <img class="badgelogo" src="/assets/mastodon.png" /><span
          >flq@freiburg.social</span
        >
      </a>
      <a class="badge" href="https://github.com/flq">
        <picture>
          <source
            srcset="/assets/github-white.png"
            media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
          />
          <img src="/assets/github-black.png" class="badgelogo" />
        </picture>
        <span>flq@github.com</span>
      </a>
      <a class="badge" href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/51428/flq">
        <img src="/assets/stackoverflow.png" class="badgelogo" />
        <span>flq@stackoverflow.com</span>
      </a>
      <a class="badge" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/frank-quednau-921856/">
        <img src="/assets/linkedin.png" class="badgelogo" />
        <span>flq@linkedin.com</span>
      </a>
    </aside>
  </main>
</Layout>
